children.subject: One important, but often-neglected, consideration is that compatibility of schedules is just as important as competency in coding. If you're unable to meet to create and agree on design, good coding skills will be of little use.

history.content:
Hello!
Currently a friend and I are planning on forming a team for CS162 this upcoming semester. Since the class typically allows teams of up to 4, we're searching for two more members to help us out. We are both intending to put a lot of effort into the class, so it would be ideal if you were the same. Additionally we'd like to limit the search to people who are already enrolled and are NOT considering dropping the course.

So if the above applies to you and you'd like to get the most you can out of 162 this Fall (and a good grade, hopefully) don't hesitate to comment or email me at dducharme@berkeley.edu.

If this post is still up, we're still looking!
